		{
			"text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel (Live Patch 24 for SLE 12 SP2)",
			"title": "Topic",
			"type": "Summary"
		},
		{
			"text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 4.4.121-92_92 fixes one issue.\n\nThe following security issue was fixed:\n\n- CVE-2018-10853: A KVM guest userspace to guest kernel write was fixed, which could be used by guest users to crash the guest kernel (bsc#1097108).\n",
			"title": "Details",
			"type": "General"
